                        "email": "raviteja28031990@gmail.com",
                        "username": "raviteja-b"
                    },
                    "message": "set ActivationPolicy to \"up\" when interface enabled?"
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/ethernet_interface.cpp",
                    "line": 670,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Ravi Teja",
                        "email": "raviteja28031990@gmail.com",
                        "username": "raviteja-b"
                    },
                    "message": "looks like ActivationPolicy default value is \"up\" right?"
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/ethernet_interface.cpp",
                    "line": 670,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Johnathan Mantey",
                        "email": "johnathanx.mantey@intel.com",
                        "username": "Howitzer105mm"
                    },
                    "message": "The default action, when ActivationPolicy is not written is for the NIC to be IFF_UP.\nThe defacto service configuration does not write ActivationPolicy.\nI tested \"initial state\" by erasing 00-bmc-eth1.network to confirm the NIC was active.\nI then used the Redfish commands to disable and re-enable the NIC."
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/ethernet_interface.cpp",
                    "line": 670,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Ravi Teja",
                        "email": "raviteja28031990@gmail.com",
                        "username": "raviteja-b"
                    },
                    "message": "Done"
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/network_manager.cpp",
                    "line": 500,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Ravi Teja",
                        "email": "raviteja28031990@gmail.com",
                        "username": "raviteja-b"
                    },
                    "message": "no longer using Unmanaged flag right?\ndo we still need this?\nsystemdNetworkdEnabled.insert_or_assign(ifidx, managed);"
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/network_manager.cpp",
                    "line": 500,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Johnathan Mantey",
                        "email": "johnathanx.mantey@intel.com",
                        "username": "Howitzer105mm"
                    },
                    "message": "This isn't the configuration file \"Unmanaged\" entry. Rather, I believe this to be the value reported from 'networkctl'\nIDX LINK TYPE     OPERATIONAL SETUP     \n  1 lo   loopback carrier     unmanaged\n  2 eth0 ether    routable    configured\n  3 eth1 ether    routable    configured\n  \n  So I think this is still living code."
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/network_manager.cpp",
                    "line": 500,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Ravi Teja",
                        "email": "raviteja28031990@gmail.com",
